 writes and transcript record storage\n- `redaction.rs`: string/value redaction only\n\nAvoid adding abstractions unless a second concrete use in the POC needs them.\n\n## Capture Pipeline\n\n```text\nCLI command\n  -> resolve repository and explicit transcript path\n  -> parse transcript snapshot\n  -> derive durable session/source keys\n  -> write GitMeta session metadata and transcript records\n  -> return terse output\n```\n\nThe transcript parser should not write GitMeta. The GitMeta writer should not\nknow provider-specific transcript shapes beyond the normalized record it\nreceives.\n\n## Target And Associations\n\nThe durable session object should stay on the `project` target by default. Even\nwhen future code can identify a branch, change, commit, or pull request, those\nobjects should reference project session keys rather than own transcript data.\n\nThat keeps session handoff possible before code exists and avoids bad ownership\nguesses when one agent session contributes to multiple GitButler branches.\n\nFuture relationship keys can look like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\n## GitMeta Writer\n\nThe writer is the only code that should open a `git_meta_lib::Session` or mutate\nGitMeta values. CLI/capture code may parse a `git_meta_lib::Target` before\ncalling the writer so target validation happens before repository side effects.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- open `git_meta_lib::Session`\n- write to the provided `git_meta_lib::Target`\n- maintain `gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>`\n- write session keys under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n- append redacted transcript records\n- deduplicate repeated capture by reading stored transcript record hashes\n\nThe writer should return capture counts and never print.\n\n## Privacy Boundary\n\nCapture writes shareable-ready keys but does not publish them. Serialization,\npush, fetch, and sync require a later privacy/product decision.\n\nEven before publishing, transcripts are sensitive. The POC should redact copied\nstrings before storage and should not add full transcript paths, working\ndirectories, branch names, or raw provider session ids as normalized fields.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T21:23:01.645Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}